						<summary>

						<p>On pieces of a broken stone.</p>						

						<p>Velanāṇḍu: Rājēndra-Chōḍikumāra.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land to the gods Nīlakaṇṭha-Mahādēva and Prasannakēśavadēva, on the eastern side of Māchasamudraṁ at Rāvipūṇḍi in Siripuram-12 of Koṇḍapaḍumara by the king, son of Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara Kulōttuṅgachōḍa Goṇka, on the occasion of Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti for providing various services in the temples. Further it records the gift of lands to Brāhmaṇas as <hi rend="italic">brahmapuri</hi> for conducting worship in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
